the discovery of fiction came from studying matter interactions
broadly a body remains at rest or in motion until an exerted force in an equal but opposite direction
a look into the nature of the materials on contact and their surface coatings demonstrates no direct contact takes place
atoms are frequently aligned to fit the center of a momentum frame about the center a quantity that is invariant
at scale the extent of the surface area with respect to the time that surfaces remain in contact leads to kinetic friction
for example the first major invention the wheel
invented sometime around 4200 4000 because applied the laws of physics
the idea revolves around a centered turning motion resulting in a torque force some radial distance at the point of contact with the surface
if static atomically the atoms align and a normal force is present
a torque force and a static force are present if an object begins to move
a torque force and no motion is only present if no surface to surface contact or burn out called kinetic friction
in motion the objects momentum frame shifts in the direction of travel
assuming the objects mass shifts due to torque then the static force weakens as the vertical momentum frame has decreased
in vehicles suspension adjusts and the momentum frame shifts back during acceleration
assuming a lightweight object with just enough mass for static contact
then it accelerates and the object will levitate from the surface periodically
a skippinglike motion
in this scenario external mass will have to be added to adjust the momentum frame for continuous surface contact
in relation the speed of light is said to be static
no acceleration or deceleration
instead light bends and stretches as it travels at a constant speed of 299792458 meters per second
this characteristic could possibly be described as a skippinglike motion
interaction in matter surface interactions and photon energy interactions
a matter of entropy and there will be natural logs
back in the early 90s i bought a really large galactic map from an advertisement in astronomy magazine
i hung it on my bedroom wall and it took up most of it probably about 8 feet 24m by 4 feet 12m
it had an overall black background with blue and white text and the vast majority of the stars were labeled and the dots were scaled to represent magnitude
several other celestial objects like the magellanic clouds and a few galaxies were also included
the shape of the map within the rectangular poster was of the night sky in one giant ellipse with the galactic center at the center of the map galactic north was up etc
it looked a bit like this but with a ton of labels possible only because of the maps large size
it also did not really need highlighting of the central plane since there were enough dots to show it naturally
what i liked about it was the edgeoncrosssection look instead of the artificial perspective of viewing the galaxy from a point far above the galactic plane
