hello fellow astronomers
i have been working for the past year on a python code designed to help people who are using ensemble photometry
it is called the variable and reference stars locator varsl it will help the user find steady reference stars for parts of the sky that aavso does not have in their variable star plotter
i have the link to the github page below for anyone to freely download and use
this code is intended to make the process of finding reference stars quicker and increase certainty of accuracy when using ensemble photometry for data analysis
this can be used to help with exoplanet research variable star research and any other research that relies on the use of ensemble photometry
i am hoping some of you will be able to find this helpful
