this photo was taken on august 19th 2022 at 2219 local time over central saudi arabia from an altitude of 40000 ft here is a summary of the capture details camera sony 7r iv lens fe 14mm f18 gm mount boeing 737 max9 exif 14mm 4s 18 iso 6400 the camera was steadied by pressing the lens hood against the window while my wife held a blanket over me and the entire window to block out reflections from cabin lights
the raw image was transferred to my iphone where i edited it in lightroom mobile
the edits performed were white balance increased exposure 1 stop lowered highlights boosted contrast clarity saturation and vibrance globally applied noise reduction and sharpening applied local adjustment to mask the aircraft wing to comply with the rules of this subreddit applied gradient adjustment to the sky to reduce black levels boost saturation further adjust hue and tint apply lens correction crop and straighten export as jpeg a full resolution unedited jpeg straight out of camera can be downloaded from feel free to ask any questionsoh and this is not a composite blend fake etc
i have been trying to capture something like this for years and i got lucky this time
at 40000ft on a moonless night it is totally possible to capture the milky way with exposures as short as 1 second with high iso and a modern full frame camera
