after watching this astrum video on using spot robots to explore the martian surface i wanted to see what other think of this possibility
and to also share what i think some pros and cons would be
the premise behind the video is how these robots could be the replacement for rovers with wheels
the wheels make traveling across terrain difficult and limited
the rovers also cannot help themselves as efficiently when faced with a problem such as the opportunity rover having a rock sample crumble and block the port for depositing the samples into the internal compartments
though they did solve this problem it was a difficult feat to accomplish
another problem with rovers is martian dust covering solar panels and limiting the power it can gather from the sun
spot has shown that it can correct itself from falls traverse loose and unstable terrain and move much faster than a rover
they also would be more dependent on ai for traveling and would not need as much guidance from earth which is hindered due to the delay of signals at that distance
spot robots can work as teams to assess problems and possibly fix any issues one of the bots might have such as dust inside one of their parts or wiping dust off solar panels
working as a unit would allow greater and more efficient exploration sample collection and possibly aid in building the first martian settlement
they would be able to travel in caves which rovers cannot access or map giving us a better idea of what is under the surface and what mars looks like when not faced with solar radiation since the cave could preserve these details
i think the spot rovers could be instrumental in colonization of mars
they could allow permanent settlements to exist before humans even step foot on the martian surface making it safer for human colonization of the red planet
i have heard some say the spot robots could be hindered by their complex design which could mean they fail more easily under the harsh conditions
though i think the moving parts can be shrouded to limit dust in the joints it still could be a possibility of failure
though it could be possible that a team of spots could fix the issues if one of the bots has a failure like this
power supply also could be an issue
the robots are smaller and would not really be able to gather much solar energy unless they had large panels that extended passed the frame of the body
these robots also might use power faster and need a more efficient source to operate
i have heard talks of using nuclear batteries though i do not believe there are not any at a size which could be usable on these bots
another idea might be a power station where the spot robots could recharge instead of carrying panels or a heavy battery
would love to hear others thoughts on this concept
is this the future of martian exploration or is this too complex and prone to failure
how do you think engineers will solve the shortcomings of these robots and what ramifications could this have on colonization of mars
thank you for reading this far and hope you learned something or have some interesting input on the subject
