mostly the game will be about exploration and solving scenarios encountered along the way
the setup so to make everything even more accurate i pulled all the actual star chart data for our local stellar neighborhood
every star within 40 light years away will be a place you can visit in the game
the game will be designed to take into account distances for travel and communications
communications traveling at the speed of light and depending on your upgrades to the ship knowing the distance and your ships speed capability will allow the game to accurately present the ingame time it would take to do what you set out to do
so with that in mind i had to figure out not only the distance from our star to other stars but also the distance from star x to star y i was able to do this through some formulas set up in a spreadsheet
the spreadsheet takes the stars degreeshours minutes and seconds and converts it into the stars right ascension and declination and using that plus the distance the spreadsheet calculates the stars cartesian coordinates and then uses those to figure out the distance from one star to another
that part works very well and that math is already done
what is in a name while working on the storyline i realized that an alien species would not be using earth names for stars
if you were a highly organized spacetraveling alien species how would you name your stars
if it were me i would make them addresses instead
so what is known as alpha centauri here would be known as star 219902 60834 43441 the stars right ascension declination and distance from the home star would be a perfect addressing system for the stars
the problem some of you may have already noticed the problem with this
if i am an alien species with my home star being sirius then why are all my addresses calculated using sol as the home star
so what i need help with is i need to know the formula to enter into my spreadsheet to convert earth data into sirian data
it is a triangle right
a huge space triangle
i know the direction and the distance of two lines leaving our sun
those are two sides of a triangle
the math i already did gives me the length of that third line
now i need to know the angle at which that line exits sirius
i need a formula that will give me the right ascension and declination of any given star from the home star of sirius
attached you will find a sample of the spreadsheet showing the data for sirius sol and alpha centauri
obviously right now sol is all zeros because it is the home star
you can use this data to test the formula and make sirius all zeros instead
if it works for these 3 stars it should work for all 500 stars on my spreadsheet
